Set in the 1990s, Captain Marvel follows Danvers, an Air Force officer, as she becomes one of the universe's most powerful heroes after earth gets involved in a galactic war between alien. The movie is directed by Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck.
The film also stars Samuel L. Jackson, Ben Mendelsohn, Djimon Hounsou, Lee Pace, Lashana Lynch, Gemma Chan, Algenis Perez Soto, Rune Temte, McKenna Grace, and Jude Law.

Captain Marvel is set to hit theaters on March 8, 2019.assistant

Here is a rewritten version of the text with some minor adjustments for clarity and grammar:

"Get ready for the next installment in the Marvel Cinematic Universe! The highly anticipated film, Captain Marvel, has released its first trailer. 

Set in the 1990s, the movie follows Carol Danvers, an Air Force officer who becomes one of the universe's most powerful heroes after Earth gets caught up in a galactic war between aliens. 

Directed by Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck, the film boasts an all-star cast, including Brie Larson as Captain Marvel, alongside Samuel L. Jackson, Ben Mendelsohn, Djimon Hounsou, Lee Pace, Lashana Lynch, Gemma Chan, Algenis Perez Soto, Rune Temte, McKenna Grace, and Jude Law. 

Mark your calendars - Captain Marvel is scheduled to hit theaters on March 8, 2019."
